<div id="review_2125539774" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2125539774" />
    <a title="S̶e̶a̶n̶" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40012758-s-e-a-n"><img alt="S̶e̶a̶n̶" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1566235680p2/40012758.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2125539774?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="S̶e̶a̶n̶" class="user" itemprop="url" name="S̶e̶a̶n̶" href="/user/show/40012758-s-e-a-n">S̶e̶a̶n̶</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780810135369" href="/book/show/32072611-fog">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40012758-s-e-a-n?shelf=2017">2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40012758-s-e-a-n?shelf=somewhere-else">somewhere-else</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2125539774" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11776954146406310838"><br/>First published in Spain in 1914, though written even earlier, this proto-Modernist classic appears to have been somewhat slow in making its way into translation. Featuring an engaging protagonist seeking love amid a miasma of existential despair, the novel unfolds with flawless pacing, peppered with humor both pithy and subtle, and infused with a measured degree of pathos. If that’s not enough to draw you in, there’s also an endearing elderly uncle who espouses his own brand of ‘mystical anarch</span>
  <span id="freeText11776954146406310838" style="display:none"><br />First published in Spain in 1914, though written even earlier, this proto-Modernist classic appears to have been somewhat slow in making its way into translation. Featuring an engaging protagonist seeking love amid a miasma of existential despair, the novel unfolds with flawless pacing, peppered with humor both pithy and subtle, and infused with a measured degree of pathos. If that’s not enough to draw you in, there’s also an endearing elderly uncle who espouses his own brand of ‘mystical anarchism’ and a rather thoughtful dog. All of this is presented with a clever metafictional flourish, adding another layer of consideration to an already compelling story. Unamuno’s prose here has been newly rendered into English with great finesse by Elena Barcia, which will hopefully increase its readership in translation.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11776954146406310838" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


